---
import CardGrid from '../components/CardGrid.astro';
import RuleCallout from '../components/RuleCallout.astro';
import ContentLayout from '../layouts/ContentLayout.astro';
---

<ContentLayout
  title="Start Here"
  summary="A plain-language introduction for prospective players, curious friends, and demo guests."
  eyebrow="New players"
  audience="public"
  ctaPrimary={{ label: 'Create a Character', href: '/player-guide/character-creation' }}
  ctaSecondary={{ label: 'Pick a Pre-Gen', href: '/pregens' }}
>
  <section class="split">
    <div class="section content-prose">
      <p class="section-label">What Kind Of Game Is This?</p>
      <h2>Weird western fantasy with cosmic horror, broken worlds, and fate riding shotgun.</h2>
      <p>
        <strong>Ka-Tet: The Path of the Beam</strong> is a tabletop RPG inspired by{' '}
        <em>The Dark Tower</em>. Players form a <strong>ka-tet</strong>: a small group bound
        together deeply enough to matter to the universe. The tone blends frontier grit, haunted
        myth, strange technology, psychic visions, and the constant feeling that the world has
        moved on without becoming less dangerous.
      </p>
      <p>
        You do not need to know the books to play. The site is built to teach the setting in
        player-safe language, starting with the terms and choices you actually need at the table.
      </p>
    </div>
    <RuleCallout
      title="What Players Do"
      points={[
        'Travel dangerous roads through Mid-World and stranger places beyond it',
        'Protect fragile towns, relics, people, and each other',
        'Face gunfights, thinnies, psychic fallout, cults, ruins, and prophecy',
        'Choose when to trust ka and when to defy it',
      ]}
    />
  </section>

  <section class="section content-prose">
    <p class="section-label">Core Terms</p>
    <table>
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th>Term</th>
          <th>Meaning</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td>Ka</td>
          <td>Fate in motion. Not mercy, but pressure that keeps the wheel turning.</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Ka-Tet</td>
          <td>A group bound together deeply enough to become a force in the story.</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Beam</td>
          <td>A great line of force that keeps worlds, time, and reality from breaking apart.</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Thinny</td>
          <td>A weak place in reality where the world sounds wrong before it tears open.</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Todash</td>
          <td>The unstable between-space reached through certain doors, rituals, and disasters.</td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </section>

  <section class="split">
    <div class="section content-prose">
      <p class="section-label">Tone And Themes</p>
      <ul>
        <li>The world is cruel, but not empty of hope.</li>
        <li>Violence is fast, loud, and usually changes everything around it.</li>
        <li>Old machines, old vows, and old sins still shape the present.</li>
        <li>Destiny can save you, but it can also demand something from you.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="section content-prose">
      <p class="section-label">Where Play Happens</p>
      <ul>
        <li>The Callas and border towns with western frontier pressure</li>
        <li>Lud and other ruins where old technology refuses to die quietly</li>
        <li>Thunderclap and the badlands near the Red’s machinery</li>
        <li>Roads along the Beam where dreams, omens, and danger converge</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="split">
    <div class="section content-prose">
      <p class="section-label">What A Session Feels Like</p>
      <ul>
        <li>A tense arrival in a town that already knows it needs help</li>
        <li>Quiet campfire talk that changes the meaning of the next fight</li>
        <li>Sudden, dangerous violence where cover, nerve, and ammunition matter</li>
        <li>A strange sign, dream, or door that makes the whole group rethink the road</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="section content-prose">
      <p class="section-label">Next Steps</p>
      <CardGrid
        cards={[
          {
            title: 'Create a Character',
            summary: 'Build from concept to stats, equipment, and party bonds.',
            href: '/player-guide/character-creation',
          },
          {
            title: 'Pick a Pre-Gen',
            summary: 'Jump into a demo with a polished ready-to-play character.',
            href: '/pregens',
          },
          {
            title: 'Read Ka Points',
            summary: 'Understand the signature fate mechanic in two minutes.',
            href: '/player-guide/rules/ka-points',
          },
          {
            title: 'Join a Demo',
            summary: 'Tell the GM what kind of game and schedule works for you.',
            href: '/join-a-game',
          },
        ]}
      />
    </div>
  </section>
</ContentLayout>
